treatment.description:
Shrubs or trees, 2–7(–10) m. Stems: (bark flaking in plates), branches ± brittle at
        base. Leaves: stipules on late ones and vigorous shoots foliaceous, apex acute to acuminate;
        petiole with paired, clustered, or stalked spherical glands or foliaceous glands distally;
        largest medial blade hypostomatous, abaxial surface glaucous or not; juvenile blade
        puberulent or pubescent abaxially, hairs white and ferruginous. Pistillate floral bracts
        persistent or deciduous after flowering. Staminate flowers: stamens 3 or, rarely, 2; anthers
        (dry), 0.4–0.6 mm. Pistillate flowers: adaxial nectary shorter than stipe; stipe 1–2 mm;
        ovary glabrous.
